Package Concepts

Class DataCarrier

  • java.lang.Object
    • Concepts.DataCarrier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class DataCarrier
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Instances of this class can be used to fill them with data, transfer them via sockets, and inject them at the destination system into a context. The DataCarrier is filled by the add... methods. It then can be serialized, sent to a destination, deserialized. By calling addToContext the data are then inserted into the Context of the target system. Created by ohlbach on 02.04.2016.
